Males of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFE61FABED97939A6" authorityName="Rios-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff" authorityYear="2018" box="[414,554,1391,1417]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ramirezi">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFE61FABED97939A6" box="[414,554,1391,1417]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. ramirezi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="E54DDF8DFFCBCE1BFDB9FABFDA693980" author="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A." pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 83" refId="ref140496" refString="Rios-Tamayo, D. &amp; Goloboff, P. A. (2018) Taxonomic revision and morphology of the trapdoor spider genus Actinopus (Mygalomorphae: Actinopodidae) in Argentina. Bulletin of the American Museum of Natural History, 419, 1 - 83. https: // doi. org / 10.1206 / 0003 - 0090 - 419.1.1" type="journal article" year="2018">Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 32 D–F) differ from those of most species of the 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFED8FA68DA2639FD" box="[295,373,1465,1491]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinhao">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFED8FA68DA2639FD" box="[295,373,1465,1491]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">pinhao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by PA continuous to PI. They resemble those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFEB0FA0EDAFE39D7" box="[335,429,1503,1529]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ducke">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFEB0FA0EDAFE39D7" box="[335,429,1503,1529]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. ducke</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FFCBCE1BFE44FA0ED95A39D4" box="[443,521,1503,1530]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="42.[136,235,1270,1294]" captionTargetBox="[172,1425,210,1213]" captionTargetId="figure-320@42.[151,1436,189,1246]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 35. Actinopus ducke sp. nov., male: A–C MCN 24987: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated Area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597311/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
