</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FFCBCE1BFE83F9D5DA9F3A30" box="[380,460,1540,1566]" captionStart="FIGURE 62" captionStartId="70.[136,235,1176,1200]" captionTargetBox="[168,1430,200,1131]" captionTargetId="figure-309@70.[151,1435,189,1152]" captionTargetPageId="70" captionText="FIGURE 62. Actinopus cornelli sp. nov., male: A–C MCN 23400: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597367" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597367/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 62</figureCitation>
A–C) and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFDB9F9D4D9EF3A30" authorityName=": Simon" authorityYear="1892" box="[582,700,1541,1567]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="insignis">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFDB9F9D4D9EF3A30" box="[582,700,1541,1567]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. insignis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Ríos-Tamayo &amp; Goloboff, 2018, fig. 45 B–D) by PA continuous to PAc. They differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFDFAF981D9363A44" box="[517,613,1616,1642]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ducke">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFDFAF981D9363A44" box="[517,613,1616,1642]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. ducke</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FFCBCE1BFD8AF981D9953A44" box="[629,710,1615,1642]" captionStart="FIGURE 35" captionStartId="42.[136,235,1270,1294]" captionTargetBox="[172,1425,210,1213]" captionTargetId="figure-320@42.[151,1436,189,1246]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="FIGURE 35. Actinopus ducke sp. nov., male: A–C MCN 24987: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated Area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597311" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597311/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 35</figureCitation>
A–C) and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFF45F9A7DA6E3AA1" box="[186,317,1653,1680]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="confusus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFF45F9A7DA6E3AA1" box="[186,317,1653,1680]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. confusus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FFCBCE1BFEB0F9A4DAF13AA1" box="[335,418,1653,1679]" captionStart="FIGURE 44" captionStartId="51.[136,235,1254,1278]" captionTargetBox="[166,1423,225,1208]" captionTargetId="figure-347@51.[151,1435,189,1230]" captionTargetPageId="51" captionText="FIGURE 44. Actinopus confusus sp. nov., male: A–C CHNUFPI 234: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated Area. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597331" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597331/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 44</figureCitation>
A–C) by BTA placed ventrally on prolateral tegular surface. They resemble those ofs 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFD0DF94ADB853AF4" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinhao">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFD0DF94ADB853AF4" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. pinhao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FFCBCE1BFF17F911DA683AF4" box="[232,315,1728,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 32" captionStartId="39.[136,235,999,1023]" captionTargetBox="[193,1392,202,952]" captionTargetId="figure-18@39.[189,1398,189,976]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURE 32. Actinopus pinhao sp. nov., male: A–C MZSP 14718: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PI-Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrow: Swelling. Scale line: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597305/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
A–C) and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFE43F910D96B3AF4" box="[444,568,1728,1755]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFE43F910D96B3AF4" box="[444,568,1728,1755]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FFCBCE1BFDB5F911D9CE3AF4" box="[586,669,1728,1754]" captionStart="FIGURE 37" captionStartId="44.[136,235,1155,1179]" captionTargetBox="[195,1400,205,1116]" captionTargetId="figure-425@44.[151,1436,189,1132]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 37. Actinopus hirsutus sp. nov., male:A–D MCN:A. Patella III, dorsal; B. Tibia III, dorsal; C. Patella IV, dorsal; D. Tibia IV, dorsal." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597315" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597315/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 37</figureCitation>
A–D) by hirsute legs, differing from 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFE39F937D9653B2E" box="[454,566,1766,1792]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pinhao">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFE39F937D9653B2E" box="[454,566,1766,1792]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. pinhao</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of tegular swelling above PA and from 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFDD3F8DDD9F43B0B" box="[556,679,1803,1830]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFDD3F8DDD9F43B0B" box="[556,679,1803,1830]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by BTA most pronounced, PA less pronounced and a serrated area developed, extending to the base of the embolus and arranged in three rows. Females differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFD0DF8ADDBAB3B92" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pampulha">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFD0DF8ADDBAB3B92" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. pampulha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FFCBCE1BFEF4F873DA2D3B92" box="[267,382,1954,1980]" captionStart="FIGURE 49" captionStartId="56.[136,235,1496,1520]" captionTargetBox="[168,1425,206,1458]" captionTargetId="figure-188@56.[151,1435,189,1472]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURE 49. Actinopus pampulha sp. nov., male: A–C UFMG 5389: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D ex-UFMG 6064: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597339" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597339/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 49 D</figureCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFE3BF873D9073B92" box="[452,596,1954,1980]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candango">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFE3BF873D9073B92" box="[452,596,1954,1980]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. candango</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="19E7BEF9FFCBCE1BFD97F873D9883B92" box="[616,731,1953,1980]" captionStart="FIGURE 54" captionStartId="61.[136,235,1744,1768]" captionTargetBox="[174,1376,210,1681]" captionTargetId="figure-83@61.[151,1435,189,1721]" captionTargetPageId="61" captionText="FIGURE 54. Actinopus candango sp. nov., male: A–C MZSP 22109: A. Copulatory bulb, prolateral; B. Copulatory bulb, dorsal; C. Copulatory bulb, retrolateral. PA-Paraembolic apophysis; BTA-Basal Tegular Apophysis; PAc-Prolateral Accessory keel; PI- Prolateral Inferior keel; PS-Prolateral Superior keel; Arrows: Serrated area. Paratype, female: D MZSP 22109: D. Spermathecae, dorsal view. Scales lines: 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5597349" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5597349/files/figure.png" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Fig. 54 D</figureCitation>
) by pore distribution reaching only 75% of the receptacles length; and from 
<taxonomicName id="46DCD9FFFFCBCE1BFEAFF83CDABB3429" box="[336,488,2029,2055]" class="Arachnida" family="Actinopodidae" genus="Actinopus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paraitinga">
<emphasis id="B3A87E6EFFCBCE1BFEAFF83CDABB3429" box="[336,488,2029,2055]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">A. paraitinga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the absence of lateral swelling on receptacles.
</paragraph>
